Note:
Runa Core Semantic Algorithms Test Suite

This test suite validates the critical algorithmic implementations:
- AST Visitor Pattern
- Hindley-Milner Type Inference
- Circular Dependency Detection
- Centralized Diagnostics

These are the foundation of the semantic analysis system.
:End Note

Note: Import dependencies
Import "../../../src/compiler/semantic/visitor.runa"
Import "../../../src/compiler/semantic/type_inference.runa"
Import "../../../src/compiler/semantic/dependency_analyzer.runa"
Import "../../../src/compiler/semantic/diagnostics.runa"

Note: Test Configuration
Let test_config be dictionary containing:
    total_tests as 0
    passed_tests as 0
    failed_tests as 0
    performance_tests as 0
    edge_case_tests as 0
    error_recovery_tests as 0

Note: Test Runner
Process called "run_all_core_algorithm_tests":
    Note: Run all core algorithm tests
    Display "🧠 Starting Runa Core Algorithm Test Suite..."
    Display ""
    
    Note: AST Visitor Pattern Tests
    Call run_test with test_name as "AST Visitor Creation" and test_function as test_ast_visitor_creation
    Call run_test with test_name as "AST Traversal" and test_function as test_ast_traversal
    Call run_test with test_name as "Visitor Method Dispatch" and test_function as test_visitor_method_dispatch
    Call run_test with test_name as "Cycle Detection in AST" and test_function as test_ast_cycle_detection
    Call run_test with test_name as "Depth Limiting" and test_function as test_ast_depth_limiting
    
    Note: Type Inference Tests
    Call run_test with test_name as "Type Inference Engine Creation" and test_function as test_type_inference_creation
    Call run_test with test_name as "Literal Type Inference" and test_function as test_literal_type_inference
    Call run_test with test_name as "Variable Type Inference" and test_function as test_variable_type_inference
    Call run_test with test_name as "Binary Operation Type Inference" and test_function as test_binary_operation_inference
    Call run_test with test_name as "Function Call Type Inference" and test_function as test_function_call_inference
    
    Note: Type Unification Tests
    Call run_test with test_name as "Basic Type Unification" and test_function as test_basic_unification
    Call run_test with test_name as "Variable Unification" and test_function as test_variable_unification
    Call run_test with test_name as "Function Type Unification" and test_function as test_function_unification
    Call run_test with test_name as "Occurs Check" and test_function as test_occurs_check
    Call run_test with test_name as "Constraint Solving" and test_function as test_constraint_solving
    
    Note: Dependency Analysis Tests
    Call run_test with test_name as "Dependency Graph Creation" and test_function as test_dependency_graph_creation
    Call run_test with test_name as "Simple Cycle Detection" and test_function as test_simple_cycle_detection
    Call run_test with test_name as "Complex Cycle Detection" and test_function as test_complex_cycle_detection
    Call run_test with test_name as "Import Dependency Analysis" and test_function as test_import_dependency_analysis
    Call run_test with test_name as "Function Dependency Analysis" and test_function as test_function_dependency_analysis
    
    Note: Diagnostic Engine Tests
    Call run_test with test_name as "Diagnostic Engine Creation" and test_function as test_diagnostic_engine_creation
    Call run_test with test_name as "Error Reporting" and test_function as test_error_reporting
    Call run_test with test_name as "Warning Reporting" and test_function as test_warning_reporting
    Call run_test with test_name as "Context Management" and test_function as test_context_management
    Call run_test with test_name as "LSP Integration" and test_function as test_lsp_integration
    
    Note: Performance Tests
    Call run_performance_test with test_name as "Large AST Traversal" and test_function as test_large_ast_traversal
    Call run_performance_test with test_name as "Complex Type Inference" and test_function as test_complex_type_inference
    Call run_performance_test with test_name as "Large Dependency Graph" and test_function as test_large_dependency_graph
    
    Note: Edge Case Tests
    Call run_edge_case_test with test_name as "Empty AST" and test_function as test_empty_ast
    Call run_edge_case_test with test_name as "Deep Nesting" and test_function as test_deep_nesting
    Call run_edge_case_test with test_name as "Circular References" and test_function as test_circular_references
    
    Note: Error Recovery Tests
    Call run_error_recovery_test with test_name as "Type Inference Errors" and test_function as test_type_inference_errors
    Call run_error_recovery_test with test_name as "Dependency Analysis Errors" and test_function as test_dependency_analysis_errors
    Call run_error_recovery_test with test_name as "Visitor Errors" and test_function as test_visitor_errors
    
    Note: Display test summary
    Display ""
    Display "📊 Core Algorithm Test Summary:"
    Display "   Total Tests: " plus test_config.total_tests
    Display "   Passed: " plus test_config.passed_tests
    Display "   Failed: " plus test_config.failed_tests
    Display "   Performance Tests: " plus test_config.performance_tests
    Display "   Edge Case Tests: " plus test_config.edge_case_tests
    Display "   Error Recovery Tests: " plus test_config.error_recovery_tests
    Display ""
    
    Let success_rate be (test_config.passed_tests divided by test_config.total_tests) multiplied by 100
    Display "   Success Rate: " plus success_rate plus "%"
    
    If test_config.failed_tests is equal to 0:
        Display "🎉 All core algorithm tests passed!"
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display "⚠️  Some core algorithm tests failed. Please review the errors above."
        Return false

Note: AST Visitor Pattern Tests
Process called "test_ast_visitor_creation":
    Note: Test AST visitor creation
    Let visitor be create_ast_visitor
    
    Assert visitor is not None
    Assert visitor.depth is equal to 0
    Assert visitor.max_depth is equal to 1000
    Assert length of visitor.visited_nodes is equal to 0
    Assert length of visitor.context_stack is equal to 0
    
    Return true

Process called "test_ast_traversal":
    Note: Test basic AST traversal
    Let visitor be create_ast_visitor
    Let mock_node be create_mock_ast_node with type as "Literal" and value as "42"
    Let context be dictionary containing "test" as "value"
    
    Let result be visit_ast with visitor as visitor and node as mock_node and context as context
    
    Assert result.success is true
    Assert result.result is equal to "42"
    Assert length of result.errors is equal to 0
    Assert visitor.performance_metrics.nodes_visited is equal to 1
    
    Return true

Process called "test_visitor_method_dispatch":
    Note: Test visitor method dispatch
    Let visitor be create_ast_visitor
    Let custom_visitor be create_custom_test_visitor
    Let mock_node be create_mock_ast_node with type as "Identifier" and value as "test_var"
    Let context be dictionary containing
    
    Let result be visit_ast with visitor as custom_visitor and node as mock_node and context as context
    
    Assert result.success is true
    Assert result.result is equal to "CUSTOM_VISIT: test_var"
    
    Return true

Process called "test_ast_cycle_detection":
    Note: Test cycle detection in AST traversal
    Let visitor be create_ast_visitor
    Let cyclic_node be create_cyclic_ast_node
    Let context be dictionary containing
    
    Let result be visit_ast with visitor as visitor and node as cyclic_node and context as context
    
    Assert result.success is true
    Assert visitor.performance_metrics.cache_hits is greater than 0
    
    Return true

Process called "test_ast_depth_limiting":
    Note: Test AST depth limiting
    Let visitor be create_ast_visitor
    Set visitor.max_depth to 5
    Let deep_node be create_deep_ast_node with depth as 10
    Let context be dictionary containing
    
    Let result be visit_ast with visitor as visitor and node as deep_node and context as context
    
    Assert result.success is false
    Assert visitor.performance_metrics.max_depth_reached is greater than 0
    
    Return true

Note: Type Inference Tests
Process called "test_type_inference_creation":
    Note: Test type inference engine creation
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    
    Assert inference_engine is not None
    Assert length of inference_engine.type_variables is equal to 0
    Assert length of inference_engine.constraints is equal to 0
    Assert length of inference_engine.substitution is equal to 0
    
    Return true

Process called "test_literal_type_inference":
    Note: Test literal type inference
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    Let number_node be create_mock_ast_node with type as "Literal" and value as "42"
    
    Let result be infer_type with context as inference_engine and expression as number_node
    
    Assert result.success is true
    Assert result.type.name is equal to "Number"
    
    Return true

Process called "test_variable_type_inference":
    Note: Test variable type inference
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    Let var_node be create_mock_ast_node with type as "Identifier" and value as "x"
    
    Let result be infer_type with context as inference_engine and expression as var_node
    
    Assert result.success is false  Note: Undefined variable
    Assert result.type.kind is equal to "variable"
    
    Return true

Process called "test_binary_operation_inference":
    Note: Test binary operation type inference
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    Let bin_op_node be create_binary_operation_node
    
    Let result be infer_type with context as inference_engine and expression as bin_op_node
    
    Assert result.success is true
    Assert result.type.name is equal to "Number"
    
    Return true

Process called "test_function_call_inference":
    Note: Test function call type inference
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    Let func_call_node be create_function_call_node
    
    Let result be infer_type with context as inference_engine and expression as func_call_node
    
    Assert result.success is true
    Assert result.type.kind is equal to "variable"  Note: Return type variable
    
    Return true

Note: Type Unification Tests
Process called "test_basic_unification":
    Note: Test basic type unification
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    Let type1 be create_primitive_type with name as "Number"
    Let type2 be create_primitive_type with name as "Number"
    
    Let result be unify_types with context as inference_engine and type1 as type1 and type2 as type2
    
    Assert result.success is true
    Assert length of result.errors is equal to 0
    
    Return true

Process called "test_variable_unification":
    Note: Test variable unification
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    Let var_type be create_fresh_type_variable with context as inference_engine and name as "T"
    Let number_type be create_primitive_type with name as "Number"
    
    Let result be unify_types with context as inference_engine and type1 as var_type and type2 as number_type
    
    Assert result.success is true
    Assert var_type.name is in result.substitution
    Assert result.substitution at key var_type.name is equal to number_type
    
    Return true

Process called "test_function_unification":
    Note: Test function type unification
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    Let func1 be create_function_type with parameter_types as list containing create_primitive_type with name as "Number" and return_type as create_primitive_type with name as "String"
    Let func2 be create_function_type with parameter_types as list containing create_primitive_type with name as "Number" and return_type as create_primitive_type with name as "String"
    
    Let result be unify_types with context as inference_engine and type1 as func1 and type2 as func2
    
    Assert result.success is true
    
    Return true

Process called "test_occurs_check":
    Note: Test occurs check for infinite types
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    Let var_type be create_fresh_type_variable with context as inference_engine and name as "T"
    
    Let result be occurs_check with context as inference_engine and var_name as var_type.name and type as var_type
    
    Assert result is true
    
    Return true

Process called "test_constraint_solving":
    Note: Test constraint solving
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    Let constraint be create_type_constraint with left as create_primitive_type with name as "Number" and right as create_primitive_type with name as "Number" and location as create_mock_location and context as "test"
    Add constraint to inference_engine.constraints
    
    Let result be solve_constraints with context as inference_engine
    
    Assert result.success is true
    
    Return true

Note: Dependency Analysis Tests
Process called "test_dependency_graph_creation":
    Note: Test dependency graph creation
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let graph be create_dependency_graph with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    
    Assert graph is not None
    Assert length of graph.nodes is equal to 0
    Assert length of graph.edges is equal to 0
    Assert length of graph.cycles is equal to 0
    
    Return true

Process called "test_simple_cycle_detection":
    Note: Test simple cycle detection
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let graph be create_dependency_graph with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    
    Note: Create simple cycle: A -> B -> A
    Let node_a be add_dependency_node with graph as graph and name as "A" and kind as "module" and location as create_mock_location
    Let node_b be add_dependency_node with graph as graph and name as "B" and kind as "module" and location as create_mock_location
    Call add_dependency_edge with graph as graph and from_name as "A" and to_name as "B"
    Call add_dependency_edge with graph as graph and from_name as "B" and to_name as "A"
    
    Let result be find_cycles with graph as graph
    
    Assert result.success is false
    Assert length of result.cycles is equal to 1
    
    Return true

Process called "test_complex_cycle_detection":
    Note: Test complex cycle detection
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let graph be create_dependency_graph with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    
    Note: Create complex cycle: A -> B -> C -> A
    Let node_a be add_dependency_node with graph as graph and name as "A" and kind as "module" and location as create_mock_location
    Let node_b be add_dependency_node with graph as graph and name as "B" and kind as "module" and location as create_mock_location
    Let node_c be add_dependency_node with graph as graph and name as "C" and kind as "module" and location as create_mock_location
    Call add_dependency_edge with graph as graph and from_name as "A" and to_name as "B"
    Call add_dependency_edge with graph as graph and from_name as "B" and to_name as "C"
    Call add_dependency_edge with graph as graph and from_name as "C" and to_name as "A"
    
    Let result be find_cycles with graph as graph
    
    Assert result.success is false
    Assert length of result.cycles is equal to 1
    Assert length of result.cycles at index 0 is equal to 3
    
    Return true

Process called "test_import_dependency_analysis":
    Note: Test import dependency analysis
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let graph be create_dependency_graph with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    Let import_node be create_mock_import_node
    
    Let result be analyze_import_dependencies with graph as graph and ast as import_node
    
    Assert length of result is equal to 1
    
    Return true

Process called "test_function_dependency_analysis":
    Note: Test function dependency analysis
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let graph be create_dependency_graph with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    Let func_call_node be create_mock_function_call_node
    
    Let result be analyze_function_dependencies with graph as graph and ast as func_call_node
    
    Assert length of result is equal to 0  Note: No current function context
    
    Return true

Note: Diagnostic Engine Tests
Process called "test_diagnostic_engine_creation":
    Note: Test diagnostic engine creation
    Let engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    
    Assert engine is not None
    Assert engine.max_errors is equal to 100
    Assert engine.max_warnings is equal to 200
    Assert engine.error_count is equal to 0
    Assert engine.warning_count is equal to 0
    
    Return true

Process called "test_error_reporting":
    Note: Test error reporting
    Let engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let error be create_undefined_variable_error with variable_name as "x" and location as create_mock_location
    
    Call report_semantic_error with engine as engine and error as error
    
    Assert engine.error_count is equal to 1
    Assert length of engine.errors is equal to 1
    Assert engine.errors at index 0.code is equal to "E001"
    
    Return true

Process called "test_warning_reporting":
    Note: Test warning reporting
    Let engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let warning be create_unused_variable_warning with variable_name as "x" and location as create_mock_location
    
    Call report_semantic_warning with engine as engine and warning as warning
    
    Assert engine.warning_count is equal to 1
    Assert length of engine.warnings is equal to 1
    Assert engine.warnings at index 0.code is equal to "W001"
    
    Return true

Process called "test_context_management":
    Note: Test context management
    Let engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let context be dictionary containing "test" as "value"
    
    Call push_context with engine as engine and context as context
    Assert length of engine.context_stack is equal to 1
    
    Let popped_context be pop_context with engine as engine
    Assert popped_context at key "test" is equal to "value"
    Assert length of engine.context_stack is equal to 0
    
    Return true

Process called "test_lsp_integration":
    Note: Test LSP integration
    Let engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let error be create_undefined_variable_error with variable_name as "x" and location as create_mock_location
    Call report_semantic_error with engine as engine and error as error
    
    Call enable_lsp_mode with engine as engine
    Let lsp_diagnostics be get_lsp_diagnostics with engine as engine
    
    Assert length of lsp_diagnostics is equal to 1
    Assert lsp_diagnostics at index 0.severity is equal to 1  Note: Error
    
    Return true

Note: Performance Tests
Process called "test_large_ast_traversal":
    Note: Test large AST traversal performance
    Let visitor be create_ast_visitor
    Let large_ast be create_large_ast with size as 1000
    Let context be dictionary containing
    
    Let start_time be get_current_time_ms
    Let result be visit_ast with visitor as visitor and node as large_ast and context as context
    Let end_time be get_current_time_ms
    
    Let traversal_time be end_time minus start_time
    Assert traversal_time is less than 1000  Note: Should complete within 1 second
    Assert result.success is true
    
    Return true

Process called "test_complex_type_inference":
    Note: Test complex type inference performance
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    Let complex_expression be create_complex_expression
    
    Let start_time be get_current_time_ms
    Let result be infer_type with context as inference_engine and expression as complex_expression
    Let end_time be get_current_time_ms
    
    Let inference_time be end_time minus start_time
    Assert inference_time is less than 500  Note: Should complete within 500ms
    Assert result.success is true
    
    Return true

Process called "test_large_dependency_graph":
    Note: Test large dependency graph performance
    Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
    Let graph be create_dependency_graph with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
    
    Note: Create large graph
    For i from 1 to 100:
        Let node_name be "Node" plus i
        Let node be add_dependency_node with graph as graph and name as node_name and kind as "module" and location as create_mock_location
        If i is greater than 1:
            Call add_dependency_edge with graph as graph and from_name as node_name and to_name as "Node" plus (i minus 1)
    
    Let start_time be get_current_time_ms
    Let result be find_cycles with graph as graph
    Let end_time be get_current_time_ms
    
    Let analysis_time be end_time minus start_time
    Assert analysis_time is less than 1000  Note: Should complete within 1 second
    Assert result.success is false  Note: Should find cycles
    
    Return true

