Note: Mock Data Creation
Process called "create_mock_ast_node" that takes type as String and value as String returns ASTNode:
    Note: Create a mock AST node for testing
    Return ASTNode with:
        type as type
        value as value
        line as 1
        column as 1
        location as create_mock_location

Process called "create_mock_location" returns SourceLocation:
    Note: Create a mock source location
    Return SourceLocation with:
        file_path as "test.runa"
        line as 1
        column as 1

Process called "create_custom_test_visitor" returns ASTVisitor:
    Note: Create a custom visitor for testing
    Let visitor be create_ast_visitor
    Set visitor.visit_identifier to custom_identifier_visitor
    Return visitor

Process called "custom_identifier_visitor" that takes visitor as ASTVisitor and node as ASTNode and context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns VisitResult:
    Note: Custom identifier visitor for testing
    Return VisitResult with:
        success as true
        result as "CUSTOM_VISIT: " plus node.value
        errors as list containing
        warnings as list containing
        context_updates as dictionary containing

Process called "create_cyclic_ast_node" returns ASTNode:
    Note: Create a cyclic AST node for testing
    Let node be create_mock_ast_node with type as "Program" and value as ""
    Set node.statements to list containing node  Note: Self-reference
    Return node

Process called "create_deep_ast_node" that takes depth as Integer returns ASTNode:
    Note: Create a deeply nested AST node
    If depth is equal to 0:
        Return create_mock_ast_node with type as "Literal" and value as "leaf"
    Otherwise:
        Let child be create_deep_ast_node with depth as depth minus 1
        Let node be create_mock_ast_node with type as "Expression" and value as ""
        Set node.left to child
        Return node

Process called "create_binary_operation_node" returns ASTNode:
    Note: Create a binary operation node
    Let node be create_mock_ast_node with type as "BinaryOperation" and value as ""
    Set node.operator to "+"
    Set node.left to create_mock_ast_node with type as "Literal" and value as "1"
    Set node.right to create_mock_ast_node with type as "Literal" and value as "2"
    Return node

Process called "create_function_call_node" returns ASTNode:
    Note: Create a function call node
    Let node be create_mock_ast_node with type as "FunctionCall" and value as ""
    Set node.function to create_mock_ast_node with type as "Identifier" and value as "f"
    Set node.arguments to list containing create_mock_ast_node with type as "Literal" and value as "42"
    Return node

Process called "create_mock_import_node" returns ASTNode:
    Note: Create a mock import node
    Let node be create_mock_ast_node with type as "ImportStatement" and value as ""
    Set node.module_name to "test_module"
    Set node.imported_symbols to list containing "test_function"
    Return node

Process called "create_mock_function_call_node" returns ASTNode:
    Note: Create a mock function call node
    Let node be create_mock_ast_node with type as "FunctionCall" and value as ""
    Set node.function to create_mock_ast_node with type as "Identifier" and value as "test_func"
    Set node.arguments to list containing
    Return node

Process called "create_large_ast" that takes size as Integer returns ASTNode:
    Note: Create a large AST for performance testing
    Let root be create_mock_ast_node with type as "Program" and value as ""
    Let statements be list containing
    
    For i from 1 to size:
        Let stmt be create_mock_ast_node with type as "Statement" and value as "stmt" plus i
        Add stmt to statements
    
    Set root.statements to statements
    Return root

Process called "create_complex_expression" returns ASTNode:
    Note: Create a complex expression for type inference testing
    Let node be create_mock_ast_node with type as "BinaryOperation" and value as ""
    Set node.operator to "*"
    Set node.left to create_binary_operation_node
    Set node.right to create_function_call_node
    Return node

Process called "create_invalid_ast_node" returns ASTNode:
    Note: Create an invalid AST node for error testing
    Let node be create_mock_ast_node with type as "InvalidType" and value as ""
    Return node

Process called "create_invalid_graph_node" returns DependencyNode:
    Note: Create an invalid graph node for error testing
    Return DependencyNode with:
        name as "invalid"
        kind as "invalid"
        location as create_mock_location
        dependencies as list containing "nonexistent"
        dependents as list containing
        visited as false
        in_stack as false
        depth as 0

Process called "create_error_prone_ast_node" returns ASTNode:
    Note: Create an error-prone AST node for testing
    Let node be create_mock_ast_node with type as "ErrorProne" and value as ""
    Return node

Note: Test Helper Functions
Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Process:
    Note: Run a single test
    Set test_config.total_tests to test_config.total_tests plus 1
    
    Try:
        Let result be test_function
        If result is true:
            Set test_config.passed_tests to test_config.passed_tests plus 1
            Display "✅ " plus test_name
        Otherwise:
            Set test_config.failed_tests to test_config.failed_tests plus 1
            Display "❌ " plus test_name plus " - Failed"
    Catch error:
        Set test_config.failed_tests to test_config.failed_tests plus 1
        Display "❌ " plus test_name plus " - Error: " plus error.message

Process called "run_performance_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Process:
    Note: Run a performance test
    Set test_config.performance_tests to test_config.performance_tests plus 1
    Call run_test with test_name as test_name and test_function as test_function

Process called "run_edge_case_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Process:
    Note: Run an edge case test
    Set test_config.edge_case_tests to test_config.edge_case_tests plus 1
    Call run_test with test_name as test_name and test_function as test_function

Process called "run_error_recovery_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Process:
    Note: Run an error recovery test
    Set test_config.error_recovery_tests to test_config.error_recovery_tests plus 1
    Call run_test with test_name as test_name and test_function as test_function

Process called "Assert" that takes condition as Boolean:
    Note: Simple assertion function
    If not condition:
        Throw "Assertion failed" 